<p><b>Deepak Chopra</b> (<a href="/wiki/Hindi_language" title="Hindi language" class="mw-redirect">Hindi</a>: <span lang="hi" xml:lang="hi">दीपक चोपड़ा</span>; born October 22, 1946) is an <a href="/wiki/Indian-American" title="Indian-American" class="mw-redirect">Indian-American</a> <a href="/wiki/Medical_doctor" title="Medical doctor" class="mw-redirect">medical doctor</a> and <a href="/wiki/Writer" title="Writer">writer</a>. He has written extensively on <a href="/wiki/Spirituality" title="Spirituality">spirituality</a> and diverse topics in <a href="/wiki/Mind-body_medicine" title="Mind-body medicine" class="mw-redirect">mind-body medicine</a>. Chopra says that he has been profoundly influenced by <a href="/wiki/Jiddu_Krishnamurti" title="Jiddu Krishnamurti">Jiddu Krishnamurti</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> He has also been influenced by the teachings of <a href="/wiki/Vedanta" title="Vedanta">Vedanta</a> and the <i><a href="/wiki/Bhagavad_Gita" title="Bhagavad Gita">Bhagavad Gita</a></i>, and by the field of <a href="/wiki/Quantum_physics" title="Quantum physics" class="mw-redirect">quantum physics</a>.<sup class="noprint Template-Fact"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources&#160;since February 2009" style="white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed">citation needed</a></i>]</span></sup> Deepak Chopra has influenced the <a href="/wiki/New_Thought_Movement" title="New Thought Movement" class="mw-redirect">New Thought Movement</a> in the <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">United States</a>.<sup class="noprint Template-Fact"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources&#160;since February 2009" style="white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed">citation needed</a></i>]</span></sup></p>
